Five things to know about North Macedonia

AFP / Jul 15, 2020, 08:25 (IST)

Small and landlocked North Macedonia, which votes in a parliamentary election on Wednesday, made headlines when it changed its name to end a dispute with Greece last year.

North Macedonia, a country that changed its name

AFP / Jul 13, 2020, 08:57 (IST)

North Macedonia is home to around two million people, mostly Orthodox Slavs and an ethnic Albanian minority that makes up around a quarter of the population.
